The Vice President spoke at the annual Democratic Attorneys General Association (DAGA) event, thanking the attorneys general for their work and highlighting the importance of their role in defending consumer rights, women's reproductive freedom, and voting rights. She discussed specific examples of their work, such as defending homeowners during the foreclosure crisis, fighting against predatory lending practices, and challenging abortion bans. The Vice President emphasized the need to protect and uphold the principles of freedom and democracy in the face of threats to these rights. She urged the attorneys general to continue their fight and called on Congress to pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act. The Vice President concluded by expressing her belief in the promise of the nation and the importance of standing together in defense of democracy.